title: Appointments to the Elderly Commission
content_text:
p>
The Government today (July 28) announced the appointment of a new member and the 
re-appointment of two incumbent members to the Elderly Commission (EC). The appointments will take effect from July 30 for a term of two years. The new member, Dr John Wong Yee-him, is a psychiatrist of the Kwai Chung 
Hospital. He is an elected member of the Kowloon City District Council and a 
member of the Appeal Board Panel (Town Planning), Criminal and Law Enforcement 
Injuries Compensation Boards and Home Purchase Allowance Appeals Committee

Injuries Compensation Boards and Home Purchase Allowance Appeals Committee Panel. The two re-appointed members are Ms Anita Wong Yiu-ming and Professor Jean Woo. The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, welcomed the new appointment and re-appointments, adding that he looked forward to their contributions to the development of elderly services in Hong Kong. Dr Chow also thanked outgoing member Dr Ng Yau-yung for his valuable contributions during his tenure. The new membership list of the EC with effect from July 30 is as follows:- Chairman:
